---

## 1. Purpose

The purpose of this Password Policy is to establish guidelines for the creation, management, and protection of passwords used within the organization. Passwords are critical to maintaining the security and integrity of company systems and data.

---

## 2. Scope

This policy applies to all employees, contractors, consultants, and temporary workers who access company systems or data, both on-site and remotely.

---

## 3. Password Requirements

- Minimum Length: 12 characters
- Complexity: Must include at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one number, and one special character (e.g., `!`, `@`, `#`)
- Password Expiry: Change passwords every 90 days
- History: Do not reuse the last 5 passwords
- Lockout Threshold: Account will be locked after 5 failed login attempts within 10 minutes

---

## 4. Password Storage and Management

- Encryption: Passwords must be stored using industry-standard encryption.
- Password Managers: Employees are encouraged to use company-approved password managers for storing passwords securely.
- No Sharing: Sharing of passwords is strictly prohibited.

---

## 5. Enforcement

Failure to comply with this policy may result in disciplinary action, including termination of access, employment, or legal action, depending on the severity of the offense.

---

## 6. Review and Revision

This policy will be reviewed annually or whenever significant changes occur to security standards or technologies.

---

> _This is a sample policy created for cybersecurity portfolio purposes._
